Package: stoneTrees
Type: Package
Title: Solve Node Centric Steiner Tree Problems
Version: 1.2
Date: 21-Dec-2020
Authors@R: c(
             person("Adam", "Sardar", email = "adam@sardar.me.uk", role = c("aut", "cre", "cph"), comment = c(ORCID="0000-0002-6912-6125")),
             person("Julie", "Borgel", email = "borgel.julie@gmail.com", role = c("ctb")),
             person("Ines", "De Santiago", email = "ines.desantiago@etherapeutics.co.uk", role = c("ctb"), comment = c(ORCID="0000-0002-8172-1322"))
             )
Description: A package aimed at solving Steiner ('stone') tree problems with uniform edge weights,
    such as the Minimum Steiner Tree (MStT) and Maximum-Weight Connected Subgraph (MWCS) problems. It
    serves as an R implementation of the paper Fischetti M et al., Thinning out Steiner trees: a node-based model for uniform edge costs. Math Program Comp (2017).
